What is our daily overall clickthrough rate? How does it vary between the groups?

ClickThrough Rate (CTR), ou taxa de cliques calculado como a proporo de anuncios clicados pelos resultados exibidos. Assim: \[\begin{equation}CTR = \frac{ResultadosClicados}{TodosResultadosPesquisados}\end{equation}\]

wikimedia = read_csv("/Users/amandasouza/lab2-cp4-aminueza/data/search_data.csv")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   session_id = col_character(),
##   search_index = col_integer(),
##   session_start_timestamp = col_double(),
##   session_start_date = col_datetime(format = ""),
##   group = col_character(),
##   results = col_integer(),
##   num_clicks = col_integer(),
##   first_click = col_integer(),
##   crt = col_double()
## )
wikimedia = wikimedia %>%
  distinct(session_id, .keep_all = T) %>%
  mutate(session_start_date = round_date(session_start_date, unit = "12 hours"))
ctr_wikimedia <- wikimedia %>% 
  group_by(session_start_date, group) %>% 
  summarise(search = sum(search_index),
            click = sum(num_clicks)
  ) %>% 
  mutate(ctr = click/search * 100)

ctr_wikimedia_overall <- ctr_wikimedia %>%
  group_by(group) %>%
  summarise(crt = as.numeric(sum(ctr))) %>%
  mutate(percent = as.numeric(crt / sum(crt)))

#Adicionando uma nova linha com a soma de todos os grupos
ctr_wikimedia_overall <- rbind(ctr_wikimedia_overall, c("overall", as.numeric(colSums(ctr_wikimedia_overall[,2:2])), as.numeric(colSums(ctr_wikimedia_overall[,3:2]))))

ctr_wikimedia_overall$percent = as.numeric(as.character(ctr_wikimedia_overall$percent))

ctr_wikimedia_overall$crt = as.numeric(as.character(ctr_wikimedia_overall$crt))

ctr_wikimedia_overall %>% 
    group_by(group) %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = reorder(group, crt), y = crt, fill = group)) + 
    geom_bar(position = "dodge", aes(fill = group),
             width=.5, stat = "identity") +
   geom_text(aes(x = group, label=sprintf("%.0f%%", 
                            round(ctr_wikimedia_overall$percent * 100))),
              color="#201d1d", size=4, 
              position = position_dodge(width = 0.5), hjust = -0.25) + 
  scale_fill_manual(label=sprintf("%.1f", 
                         round(ctr_wikimedia_overall$crt)), 
                      values = alpha(c("#5a7cea","#b370bf", "#F0E442"))) +
  labs(x ="Groups", 
         y = "\nClick Through Rate (CTR)",
         fill = "CRT(AVG)") +
    coord_flip()+
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, 1.2 * max(ctr_wikimedia_overall$crt))) +
                       #breaks = seq(0, 15000, 3000)) 
    theme_bw() +
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(face="bold", size=10), 
          axis.text.y = element_text(face="bold", size=10),
          plot.title = element_text(color="#201d1d", size=12, 
                                    face="bold", hjust = 0.5),
          axis.title = element_text(color="#201d1d", 
                                    face="bold", size=11),
          panel.grid.major.y = element_blank(),
          legend.position = c(0.85, 0.2))

ctr_wikimedia %>%
  group_by(session_start_date) %>% 
  gather(key = type, value = value, 3:4) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(session_start_date, value)) +
  geom_bar(aes(fill = type), stat = "identity", position = "dodge") +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette="Set1") +
  labs(title = "C", 
       y = "Overall by day (12 hours)",
       x = NULL) + theme_classic()

ctr_wikimedia %>%
  group_by(session_start_date) %>% 
  gather(key = type, value = value, 3:4) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(session_start_date, value)) +
  geom_bar(aes(fill = type), stat = "identity", position = "dodge") +
  facet_grid(group ~ .) +scale_fill_brewer(palette="Set1") +
  labs(title = "Overall Clicks/Searches by Groups", 
       y = "Overall by day (12 hours)",
       x = NULL) + theme_classic()

ctr_wikimedia %>%
    group_by(session_start_date) %>% 
    ggplot(aes(x = session_start_date , y = ctr, color = group)) +
    scale_color_manual(labels = c("A", "B"), values = c(a = "navy", b = "red")) +
    geom_point(position = position_jitter(width = 0.2), alpha = 0.8) +
    geom_line() +
    labs(x=NULL, 
         y='Click Through Rate (CTR)',
         caption="Source: Wikimedia") +
    theme_bw() +
    theme(panel.grid.major = element_blank(), panel.grid.minor = element_blank())

ggplot(ctr_wikimedia, aes(x=session_start_date)) + 
  geom_line(aes(y=ctr, col=group)) + 
  theme_classic() +
  labs(title="Time Series of Returns Percentage", 
       subtitle="Drawn from Long Data format", 
       caption="Source: Economics", 
       y="Returns %", 
       color=NULL) +  # title and caption
